{
  "stem": "14060.4",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "They full well knew the facts.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "They were negotiating for their own safety, which, in the end, 1,200 people did get out of Budapest-- all the leaders, and so on.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "But there is a great responsibility lying on those people, who may be dead or may be still alive, who have sold out the provincial jury of entire Hungary.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Because I would like to compare them to the man who was the head of the Judenrat in Poland in Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "When he got to know-- and the Germans were doing it also, giving the Jews instructions.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "You do that.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "If you don't, you are-- we shoot you.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And so therefore, to make them for their own safety carry out the instructions.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "When he got to know that Treblinka-- which-- where the Warsaw Jews were in the main deported to-- existed, he let it be known to the-- to the Jews in the ghetto, or generally to the Polish Jews, he, he made it.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "He knew that was a death sentence for him because he, he-- that was the worst thing he could have done, as far as the Germans were concerned, to create panic, and committed suicide.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "This man I respect not because I think he should have committed suicide.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "But he probably was not in a position to escape.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And so he, he preferred it, before he gets tortured and killed, to do it.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "This is not for me to comment.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "But that is a man of integrity.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And unfortunately, the Hungarian Jewish leadership did not have this integrity.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "They can have thousands of excuses to save themselves, to save their families, fine.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "I accept it.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "Maybe I wouldn't have been different.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "But in that case, resign, and don't carry on the public duty.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
